    "body": "### Problem\n\nCurrently `vim.lsp.document_color.enable()` runs every time an LSP attaches. This makes it difficult to see when the feature will actually be present. For example I can't do:\n\n```lua\n_enable = vim.lsp.document_color.enable\nvim.lsp.document_color = function(...)\n  vim.notify('client supports textDocument/documentColor')\n  _enable(...)\nend\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nAs with other LSP features, this should be conditionally enabled based on server capabilities.\n\nThis:\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/fbb1caf5f8ce427272799b8f52e01575d72cb3e4/runtime/lua/vim/lsp.lua#L787\n\nI think should be:\n```lua\nif client:supports_method(ms.textDocument_documentColor) then \n  lsp.document_color.enable(true, bufnr)\nend\n```",
