            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "> This is just done inside the enable() logic.\n\n`enable()` itself doesn't check capabilities, but the autocmds handlers do.\nSo this is mainly a small performance gain by checking capabilities before enabling.\n\n@matystroia if you want to \"see when the feature will actually be present.\", use `document_color.is_enabled()` to check whether it's \"expected\" - this doesn't guarantee that the client supports it, since capabilities may come from dynamic registrations.\nTo ensure support, use `client:supports_method(ms.textDocument_documentColor)`. If both are true, then the feature is enabled and working.",
